=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Regulatory and Deployment Standards for Use of Vape Detection Sensors in Schools and Public Institutions
Date: 2025-11-04
Source: Singapore Parliament
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Written Answer)
Topic: Vaping, Detection Sensors, Schools, Public Institutions, Regulation

Summary:
- Question about whether vape detection sensors are used in schools and public institutions, and if so, regulatory/deployment standards including approval, technical specs, privacy safeguards, and redress.
- Ministry of Health / HSA response:
  - Vape detection sensors are currently **not used** in public institutions.
  - Some schools and Institutes of Higher Learning (IHLs) explored their use but found them unsuitable.
  - Vape detection sensors are **not regulated** by MOH or HSA.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)
- Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
- Schools and Institutes of Higher Learning (IHLs)
- Mr Hamid Razak, MP (West Coast-Jurong West GRC)

Key Concepts:
- Vape detection technology evaluation
- Regulatory and deployment standards (currently none)
- Privacy and redress considerations (not applicable)
- Institutional trials and assessment

Body:
1. No deployment of vape detection sensors in public institutions at present.
2. Some schools/IHLs explored usage but deemed unsuitable.
3. Sensors are not regulated by MOH or HSA.

Author / Issuer:
Ministry of Health (MOH), Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
Date of Issue: 2025-11-04
